HEADWORD: Kittiwake
<hw>Kit"ti*wake</hw> <pr>(k⟦icr⟧t"t⟦icr⟧*w⟦amac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A northern gull (<spn>Rissa tridactyla</spn>),
inhabiting the coasts of Europe and America. It is white, with black
tips to the wings, and has only three toes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

